A stealth ship is a sea vehicle built to be undetectable by radar and visual infrared systems. In other words, this kind of ships are built to stay unnoticed while traveling on water. The US Army has taken advantage of this modern technology by creating their very own armed stealth ship.
The M80 Stilettoan armored military ship that uses advanced stealth technology to help US soldiers travel on sea without being tracked by any radar system. The machine sports a Pentamaran hull design and has its bodyparts built from advanced carbon fiber.

The armed sea vehicle runs at a maximum speed of 110 kilometers per hour and has room to accommodate 1 rigid hull inflatable boat.
A photo of US soldiers entering the M80 Stiletto from the rear.



